<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.4.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80095" speakername="Alex Neil (Central Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S2W-15449" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#3">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what its estimate is of the consequential funding under the Barnett formula of the decision announced by the Chancellor of the Exchequer in the Budget 2005 to subsidise free local bus travel for pensioners for each of the next three financial years.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.4.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80077" speakername="Mr Tom McCabe" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#3">

  <p>The increases to the Scottish budget as a result of the allocations announced by the Chancellor in Budget 2005 to support free off-peak local area bus travel for those aged over 60 and disabled people in England from April 2006 are as follows: &pound;35.7 million in 2006-07 and &pound;37.485 million in 2007-08.</p>

</reply>


