<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.10.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80032" speakername="Ross Finnie" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">

  <p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.11.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">Waste Management</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.11.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80035" speakername="Phil Gallie (South of Scotland) (Con)" spid="S2W-15446" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether the Register of Waste Carriers is maintained on a UK-wide basis.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.11.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80032" speakername="Ross Finnie" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">

  <p>There are separate registers for Great Britain, and for Northern Ireland.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.12.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">Waste Management</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.12.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80035" speakername="Phil Gallie (South of Scotland) (Con)" spid="S2W-15447" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether the drivers of vehicles travelling not on the Register of Waste Carriers retain a duty of care for the waste they transport.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-03-30.12.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80032" speakername="Ross Finnie" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0330.htm#9">

  <p>The duty of care in Section 34 of the Environmental Protection Act 1990 applies to all who import, produce, carry, keep, treat or dispose of controlled waste.</p>

</reply>
